Remove the @Philadelphia Cheese{247.5%g} from the fridge so that it reaches room
temperature. Meanwhile, pop the butter into a #small saucepan{} on medium-low
heat and allow it to melt, then remove from the heat. Mix the
@Speculoos Biscuit Crumb{187.5%g} into the melted butter, then divide it equally
between #glasses{}, small #serving bowls{} or #ramekins{} (whichever you have to
hand, 1 per person). Pat the crumbs down to make a firm base, then set aside.

Heat 2cm of @water{} in a small saucepan on medium heat until just simmering.
Pop the @Chocolate Chips{150%g} into a #heatproof bowl{} and sit it snugly on top
of the #saucepan{}. Stir the chocolate until melted, then remove from the heat
and allow it to cool, ~{1-2%minutes}.

In a #large bowl{}, mix together the cream cheese, @Caster Sugar{75%g} and
cooled chocolate until softened and well incorporated. Gently fold in the
@Creme Fraiche{225%g} until well combined, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Divide the cheesecake filling between your glasses/bowls/ramekins, smoothing the
top with the back of a #spoon{}.

Cover and chill the cheesecake pots overnight until they have set.

When you're ready to serve, drizzle the @Salted Caramel Sauce{120%g} over each
cheesecake pot. Scatter over the @Toasted Flaked Almonds{25%g}. Tuck into your
Millionaire's Cheesecake Christmas Puddings and enjoy!

> Something sweet for afters! This indulgent festive dessert is a twist on the
> classic Millionaire's shortbread, combining layers of crunchy speculoos
> biscuit crumb, dark chocolate cheesecake filling and smooth salted caramel. A
> final sprinkling of flaked almonds make this a very merry Christmas pudding.